captions.text:
-Hi, it's Brooklyn and
I'm with my sister Kamri

and we're going to be doing
the smoothie challenge.

And it's basically where you
have 10 not-so-yummy smoothie

ingredients and ten really
good smoothie ingredients.

And we have them all labeled on
a piece of paper and you draw.

And whatever you get you
have to add to your smoothie.

And in the end, you
have to drink it.
So it's going to be nasty.
Some of our good flavors are--

-We have syrup, a banana,
yogurt, milk, whipped cream,

Hershey's chocolate sauce,
juice, peanut butter,

-And some of our bad
flavors are mustard,

and it's like a special
mustard so it's spicy.

Lemon juice, easy cheese,
pickles, peppers, baby food,
So it's going to be exciting.

Can you hand me
the strawberries?

While I'm adding these
in, do you want to draw?
I'm going to put in six.

We were like, complaining
about the tuna earlier.

We were like, whoever
gets the tuna, I am sorry.
That's going to be so gross.
-Can I just put in like, two--

-No, you have to put
in the whole thing.

-You have to put
in the whole thing.
You have to put in half.
Here, let me put it in.
-How do you even put in in?

Here, do you want
to use this spoon?
-No, you have to put in half.

-I'm just going to stick
the whole banana in there.
-Why can I not peel this banana?

You only get half
of the good flavor.

I'm like, getting
all the berries.

That means it's going to
be flavorful and yummy.

-That's actually one of
the better bad kinds.
How much of this do I put in?

Ew, I'm ruining my berries with
ketchup and chopped onions.

-I think it's like,
rice and chicken.

How much-- just put in
like, two scoopfulls.

-Do I have to put a
whole one of these in?
-Come on, I had to do tuna.

-Hey, that's better than like,
peppers or spicy mustard.

-OK, since I already
have baby food in there,

I'm just going to
scoop this out.

-Do I shake, are you supposed
to shake whipped cream?

OK, mine's looking
pretty tasty actually.
-I got some on her nose too.

Is it my turn or
your turn to draw?

No, I think I just
drew whipped cream
so it's your turn to draw one.
-Oh look, it's still on my face.

-That's actually
kind of not that bad.
How much milk do I put in?

Probably a lot since I
don't have any liquids yet.

-Just do-- I'd pour in
like, till the eight.

Hopefully that means
it's a good one.

She's getting all
the nasty ones.

-You can add that as a
little flavor to your--

I get all the yummy ones
like chocolate sauce
to add to the whipped cream.

-I feel like I still have
whipped cream on my face.

-Oh, this is actually
kind of heavy.
This is like, all-- easy cheese.

OK, I can handle easy cheese
because it's not that bad.
-But you have to squirt a lot.

-But I have to
squirt some in, huh?
How do you even squirt it?

-Yours is going to be--
mine is going to be chunky.
OK, that just looks nasty now.

-Yours looks like a
banana sundae gone wrong.

It's got the whipped
cream and the chocolate.

-Oh no, that means I
got one of the bad ones.

-That means that you
got-- what's the last one?

-Kamri gets the
tomato-- what is this?
I don't want to use this.

-Still pouring my
maple syrup in there.

-There's like, some dark
stuff at the bottom.

Let's just make sure that
this is tomato juice.

-Ew, she's got all
the bad flavors.

-Maybe all the bad flavors makes
something good mixed together.

-But then again, it
could be disgusting
and I could barf all over.

-It could be nasty
and she could barf.
-How much of this do we put in?

You've got to put
more than that.

You put in one, you
put in one pickle.

-You put in, you
put in one pickle.

Now we're going to actually
blend the smoothies.
-Do I have to drink all of this?

Even just one sip is enough
to make me barf right now.

It tastes like, like, at first
it tastes like juice but then

you get the tuna in
there and then it's--

I literally can not
put that in my mouth.

Just swallow like,
two sips of it.

-I almost did
there for a second.

-One more sip each
and we can be done.

-I just puked, like,
almost puked there.

-One more sip each
and we can be done.

-No, we have to do
it at the same time.

I bet mine is
nastier than yours.
-I have like, a tiny bit left.

So the result of the
smoothie challenge

were I get 1/2 a wing because
I finished 1/2 my smoothie.

And Kamri epically
failed because she only

-I still have the flavor
of chopped onions, ketchup,
and peanut butter in my mouth.

-I almost had to run to
the bathroom to throw up.

You guys should leave
a comment below on what

ingredients you would
have used, good and bad,

Thank you guys so
much for watching

and we'll see you
guys next week.
